flowRoot.flowPara: Since 1993, The International World Water Day is held every year on 22 March with the objective of focusing global attention on the importance of freshwater and advocating the sustainable management of freshwater resources. The day was first formally proposed in the 1992 United Nations Conference on Environment and Development (UNCED) in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. The day has also become a popular facebook trend.
